              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nCLOSED,SEALDC\n\nU.S. District Court\nSouthern District of California (San Diego)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 3:17-cr-00095-JLS-1\n\nCase title: USA v. Saucedo Date Filed: 01/12/2017\n\nMagistrate judge case number: 3:16-mj-03834-BGS Date Terminated: 05/18/2018\n\nAssigned to: Judge Janis L. Sammartino\n\nDefendant (1)\nJoseph Saucedo represented by Kasha K. Castillo\n59312298 Federal Defenders of San Diego\nFederal Correctional Complex 225 Broadway\nPO Box 1000 Suite 900\nPetersburg, VA 23804 San Diego, CA 92101-5008\nTERMINATED: 05/18/2018 (619)234-8467\nFax: (619)687-2666\nEmail: kasha_castillo@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 03/02/2018\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Public Defender or Community Defender\nAppointment\n\nMayra L Garcia\nLaw Offices of Mayra L Garcia\n185 West F Street\nSuite 100\nSan Diego, CA 92101\n(619)238-4132\nFax: (619)342-9798\nEmail: mlg@mlgdefense.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\nFederal Defenders\nFederal Defenders of San Diego\n225 Broadway\nSuite 900\nSan Diego, CA 92101-5008\n(619)234-8467\nFax: (619)687-2666\nEmail: cassd_ecf@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 12/19/2016\nDesignation: Public Defender or Community Defender\nAppointment\n\nLeila W Morgan\nFederal Defenders of San Diego\n225 Broadway\nSuite 900\nSan Diego, CA 92101-5008\n(619)234-8467\nFax: (619)687-2666\nEmail: Leila_Morgan@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 08/09/2017\nDesignation: Public Defender or Community Defender\nAppointment\n\nPending Counts Disposition\nCustody of the BOP for 235 months as to each count 1 and 2 to\n18:2252(a)(2),(b); 28:2461(c) - Attempted Receipt and Receipt\nrun concurrent for a total of 235 months. Supervised release for\nof Child Pornography; Criminal Forfeiture\n20 years as to each count 1 and 2 to run concurrent for a total of\n(1s)\n20 years. Court imposes no assessment, fine or restitution\nCustody of the BOP for 235 months as to each count 1 and 2 to\n18:2252(a)(2),(b); 28:2461(c) - Attempted Receipt and Receipt\nrun concurrent for a total of 235 months. Supervised release for\nof Child Pornography; Criminal Forfeiture\n20 years as to each count 1 and 2 to run concurrent for a total of\n(2s)\n20 years. Court imposes no assessment, fine or restitution\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\n18:2251(a) - Use of Child to Produce Visual Depiction\nDismissed on Govt's oral motion\n(1)\n18:2251(a)(e); 28:2461(c) - Attempted Use of Child to Produce Dismissed on Govt's oral motion\nVisual Depiction and Criminal Forfeiture\n(2)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nFelony\n\nComplaints Disposition\n18:2251(a); 18:2251(a),(e); 18:2252(a)(2) - Use of Child to\nProduce a Visual Depiction; Attempted use of Child to produce\na Visual Depiction; Receipt of Images of Minors engaged in\nSexually explicit conduct\n\nPlaintiff\nUSA represented by Alexandra Foster\nU.S. Attorneys Office\n880 Front Street\nRoom 6293\nSan Diego, CA 92101\n(619) 546-6735\nEmail: Alexandra.Foster@usdoj.gov\nTERMINATED: 07/14/2017\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant United States Attorney\n\nSabrina L. Feve\nU S Attorneys Office\nSouthern District of California\n880 Front Street\nRoom 6293\nSan Diego, CA 92101\n(619)546-6786\nFax: (619)546-0831\nEmail: sabrina.feve@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant United States Attorney\n\nDate Filed # Docket Text\n12/14/2016 1 COMPLAINT (t/w Warrant) as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo (1). (lao) (sjt). (dlg-v) (12/16/2016 - Added image. Case unsealed 12/15/2016.)\n(mdc) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/14/2016)\n12/14/2016 2 ARREST WARRANT ISSUED by Magistrate Judge Andrew G. Schopler in case as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo. (lao) (dlg-v) (12/16/2016 -\nAdded image. Case unsealed 12/15/2016.) (mdc) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/14/2016)\n12/14/2016 3 MOTION to Seal Arrest Warrant, Complaint, Affidavit and Order thereon by USA as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo. (lao) (dlg-v) (12/16/2016 -\nAdded image. Case unsealed 12/15/2016.) (mdc) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/14/2016)\n12/14/2016 4 ORDER Sealing Arrest Warrant, Complaint, Affidavit, Motion and Order thereon re (Docket entry 3 ) as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo (1).\nSigned by Magistrate Judge Andrew G. Schopler on 12/14/16. (lao) (dlg-v) (12/16/2016 - Added image. Case unsealed 12/15/2016.) (mdc)\n[3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/14/2016)\n12/15/2016 5 Set/Reset Duty Hearings as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo: Initial Appearance set for 12/15/2016 before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. (no\ndocument attached) (tkl) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/15/2016)\n12/15/2016 Arrest of Joseph Daniel Saucedo (no document attached) (tkl) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/15/2016)\n12/15/2016 6 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt: Initial Appearance as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo held on\n12/15/2016. Federal Defenders provisionally appointed for Joseph Daniel Saucedo. Financial Affidavit due 12/20/16. Bond set as to Joseph\nDaniel Saucedo (1) No Bail. Detention Hearing (flight/danger) set for 12/22/2016 09:00 AM before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt.\nPreliminary Hearing set for 12/29/2016 09:00 AM before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. Arraignment set for 1/12/2017 01:30 PM\nbefore Magistrate Judge Bernard G. Skomal. Magistrate Judge Andrew G. Schopler is no longer assigned to case and Magistrate Judge\nBernard G. Skomal is now assigned to the case. The new case number is 16MJ3834-BGS. Government's oral motion to unseal entire case is\ngranted. (Sealed Clerk Notified) (CD# 12/15/2016 JLB 16:2:28-2:47). (Plaintiff Attorney Alexandra Foster, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney\nMatt Binninger, FD-S/A). (no document attached) (lao) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/16/2016)\n12/15/2016 7 Oral MOTION to Detain (flight/danger) by USA as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo. (no document attached) (lao) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS]\n(Entered: 12/16/2016)\n12/15/2016 8 ***English. No Interpreter needed as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo (no document attached) (lao) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/16/2016)\n12/19/2016 9 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Leila W Morgan appearing for Joseph Daniel Saucedo (Morgan, Leila)Attorney Leila W\nMorgan added to party Joseph Daniel Saucedo(pty:dft)(mpl). [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/19/2016)\n12/19/2016 10 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE Sabrina L. Feve appearing for USA. (Feve, Sabrina)Attorney Sabrina L. Feve added to party\nUSA(pty:pla) (mpl). [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/19/2016)\n12/19/2016 11 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE Alexandra Foster appearing for USA. (Foster, Alexandra)Attorney Alexandra Foster added to\nparty USA(pty:pla) (mpl). [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/19/2016)\n12/20/2016 12 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 12/15/2016, in case as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo, re 2 Warrant Issued. (mpl)(jao). [3:16-mj-03834-\nBGS] (Entered: 12/21/2016)\n12/22/2016 13 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt:finding as moot 7 Motion to Detain as to Joseph Daniel\nSaucedo (1); Detention Hearing as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo noy held on 12/22/2016. Dft stipulates to detention pending trial w/o\nprejudice; Govt to submit proposed order; Preliminary Hearing Continued as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo. Defense oral motion to continue\nhearing granted.( Preliminary Hearing continued to 1/12/2017 01:30 PM in Courtroom 1B before Magistrate Judge Bernard G. Skomal.).\n(CD# 12/22/2016 JLB16-9:22-9:26). (Plaintiff Attorney Sabrina Feve, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney Leila W. Morgan, FD). (no document\nattached) (rab) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/22/2016)\n12/23/2016 14 ORDER OF DETENTION as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo. Signed by Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. (mxn) Modified to include signature\non 1/11/2017 (jao). [3:16-mj-03834-BGS] (Entered: 12/27/2016)\n01/04/2017 15 NOTICE OF CHANGE OF HEARING as to Defendant Joseph Daniel Saucedo. On Court's own motion (conflict with Court's schedule) the\nArraignment is reset for 1/12/2017 09:00 AM before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. Preliminary Hearing is reset for 1/12/2017 09:00\nAM before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. ***CHANGE IN JUDGE AND TIME ONLY***(no document attached) (tml) [3:16-mj-\n03834-BGS] (Entered: 01/04/2017)\n01/10/2017 17 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 12/15/2016, in case as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo, re 2 Warrant Issued. (mpl) (jao). [3:16-mj-03834-\nBGS] (Entered: 01/11/2017)\n01/11/2017 16 NOTICE OF CHANGE OF HEARING TIME as to Defendant Joseph Daniel Saucedo. On the court's own motion the Arraignment has\nbeen reset to 1/12/2017 08:45 AM in Courtroom 1D before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. Preliminary Hearing has been reset to\n1/12/2017 08:45 AM in Courtroom 1D before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. (no document attached) (rab) [3:16-mj-03834-BGS]\n(Entered: 01/11/2017)\n01/12/2017 18 INFORMATION as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo (1) count(s) 1, 2. (rab) (Entered: 01/13/2017)\n01/12/2017 19 WAIVER OF INDICTMENT by Joseph Daniel Saucedo (rab) (Entered: 01/13/2017)\n01/12/2017 20 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt: Arraignment as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo (1) Count 1,2 of the\nInformation held on 1/12/2017; Not Guilty plea entered. Motion Hearing/Trial Setting set for 2/10/2017 01:30 PM in Courtroom 4A before\nJudge Janis L. Sammartino. (CD# 1/12/2017 JLB17-8:53-8:57). The deadline for the Financial Affidavit has been extended to 1/20/17;\n(Plaintiff Attorney Oleksandra Johnson, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney Leila W. Morgan, FD). (no document attached) (rab) Modified on\n1/13/2017 (rab). (Entered: 01/13/2017)\n01/25/2017 21 NOTICE OF CHANGE OF HEARING TIME as to Defendant Joseph Daniel Saucedo: On Court's own motion, Motion Hearing/Trial\nSetting reset from 1:30 PM to 11:00 AM on 2/10/2017 before Judge Janis L. Sammartino (no document attached) (acr) (Entered:\n01/