/2017)\n05/18/2017 30 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Defendant Joseph Daniel Saucedo. At the request of defense attorney, Change of Plea Hearing set for\n5/25/2017 at 09:00 AM in Courtroom 5C before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt. (no document attached) (cxl) (Entered: 05/18/2017)\n05/19/2017 31 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Janis L. Sammartino: Motion Hearing/Trial Setting as to Joseph Daniel Saucedo continued\non defense counsel's oral request for 6/2/2017 01:30 PM before Judge Janis L. Sammartino (Court Reporter/ECR Frank Rangus / CRD A\nRamos / AUSA Ari Fitzwater / FD Leila W. Morgan) (no document attached) (acr) (Entered: 05/19/2017)\n05/25/2017 32 SUPERSEDING INFORMATION as to Joseph Saucedo (1) count(s) 1s-2s. (cxl) (Entered: 05/26/2017)\n05/25/2017 33 WAIVER OF INDICTMENT (Superseding Information) by Joseph Saucedo (cxl) (Entered: 05/26/2017)\n05/25/2017 34 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt: Arraignment on Superseding Information as to Joseph\nSaucedo (1) Count 1s-2s held on 5/25/2017. Not Guilty plea entered. Change of Plea Hearing as to Joseph Saucedo held on 5/25/2017.\nConsent, Findings and Plea Agreement filed. Plea Tendered by Joseph Saucedo Guilty on counts 1,2 of Superseding Information.\nExcludable(s) started as to Joseph Saucedo: XT 5/25/2017 - 8/25/2017. PSR Ordered. Sentence With PSR set for 8/25/2017 at 09:00 AM\nbefore Judge Janis L. Sammartino. All other hearings vacated and motions withdrawn (CD# 5/25/2017 JLB17 10:12 - 10:24). (Plaintiff\nAttorney Alexandra Foster, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney Leila W Morgan). (no document attached) (cxl) (Entered: 05/26/2017)\n05/25/2017 35 CONSENT TO RULE 11 PLEA before Magistrate Judge Jill L. Burkhardt by Joseph Saucedo. (dxj) (Entered: 05/26/2017)\n05/25/2017 37 FINDINGS AND RECOMMENDATION of the Magistrate Judge upon a Tendered Plea of Guilty as to Joseph Saucedo: Recommending\nthat the district judge accept the defendant's plea of guilty. Signed by