by Judge Janis L. Sammartino on 10/12/2017.(mpl) (jao). (Entered:\n10/12/2017)\n12/14/2017 48 MOTION for Amended Order of Forfeiture of Property by USA as to Joseph Saucedo. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration)(Feve, Sabrina)\n(mpl). (Entered: 12/14/2017)\n12/18/2017 49 ORDER granting 48 Motion for Amended Order of Criminal Forfeiture as to Joseph Saucedo (1). Signed by Judge Janis L. Sammartino on\n12/18/2017.(acc) (Entered: 12/18/2017)\n01/08/2018 50 Joint MOTION to Continue Sentencing Hearing by Joseph Saucedo. (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered: 01/08/2018)\n01/08/2018 51 ORDER Granting 50 Joint Motion to Continue as to Joseph Saucedo (1) The Sentence With PSR is continued to 2/16/2018 at 9:00 a.m.\nbefore Judge Janis L. Sammartino. Signed by Judge Janis L. Sammartino on 1/8/2018.(mpl) (Entered: 01/08/2018)\n01/19/2018 52 OBJECTION TO PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT by Joseph Saucedo (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered: 01/19/2018)\n01/30/2018 53 ADDENDUM TO PRE-SENTENCE REPORT as to Joseph Saucedo. Report prepared by: Adam E Zimmerman. (Document applicable to\nUSA, Joseph Saucedo.) (Castillo-Ramos, M.) (mpl). (Entered: 01/30/2018)\n02/06/2018 58 Joint MOTION to Continue by Joseph Saucedo. (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered: 02/06/2018)\n02/07/2018 59 ORDER Granting 58 Joint Motion to Continue Sentencing Hearing as to Joseph Saucedo (1). The Sentence With PSR hearing is continued\nto 3/2/2018 at 10:30 a.m. before Judge Janis L. Sammartino. Signed by Judge Janis L. Sammartino on 2/7/2018.(mpl) (Entered:\n02/07/2018)\n02/12/2018 60 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Defendant Joseph Saucedo. As requested by defense counsel an Attorney Appointment Hearing is set for\n2/15/2018 01:30 PM before Magistrate Judge Bernard G. Skomal. (no document attached) (knb) (Entered: 02/12/2018)\n02/15/2018 61 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Bernard G. Skomal: Attorney Appointment Hearing as to Joseph Saucedo held\non 2/15/2018. Oral Motion by defendant for new attorney appointment - denied. (CD# 2/15/2018 BGS1:224-229). (Plaintiff Attorney\nSabrina Feve, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney Kasha Castillo, FD). (no document attached) (knb) (Entered: 02/15/2018)\n02/20/2018 62 OBJECTION TO PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT by Joseph Saucedo (Amended) (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered:\n02/20/2018)\n02/20/2018 63 SENTENCING SUMMARY CHART by Joseph Saucedo (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered: 02/20/2018)\n02/20/2018 64 Sentencing Document: Documents in Support of Sentencing by Joseph Saucedo (Castillo, Kasha) (mpl). (Entered: 02/20/2018)\n02/26/2018 65 Notice of Document Discrepancies and Order Thereon by Judge Janis L. Sammartino Rejecting Document: Objections to Magistrate\nJudge's Ruling, from Defendant Joseph Saucedo. Non-compliance with local rule(s), OTHER: Motions/Objections must be filed by attorney\nof record. (All non-registered users served via U.S. Mail Service)(mpl) (Additional attachment(s) added on 2/27/2018: # 1 Rejected\nDocument) (mpl). (Entered: 02/27/2018)\n03/02/2018 66 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Janis L. Sammartino: Status Hearing re Request for New Counsel as to Joseph Saucedo\nheld on 3/2/2018. Defendant's request for new counsel is granted. Attorney Mayra L Garcia, CJA appointed for Joseph Saucedo. Attorney\nKasha K Castillo, FD relieved in case as to Joseph Saucedo. Status Hearing re Counsel set for 3/9/2018 10:30 AM before Judge Janis L.\nSammartino. (Court Reporter/ECR Frank Rangus)(USPO Deborah Berry)(Plaintiff Attorney Sabrina Feve, AUSA). (Defendant Attorney\nKasha Castillo, FD). (no document attached) (kas) (Entered: 03/02/2018)\n03/09/2018 67 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Janis L. Sammartino: Status Hearing as to Joseph Saucedo held on 3/9/2018; Mayra L.\nGarcia accepts appointment. Sentence With PSR set for 5/11/2018 09:00 AM before Judge Janis L. Sammartino (Court Reporter/ECR\nGayle Wakefield / CRD A Ramos / AUSA Sabrina L. Feve / CJA Mayra L. Garcia) (no document attached) (acr) (Entered: 03/12/2018)\n05/04/2018 68 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM & Certificate of Service by USA as to Joseph Saucedo (Feve, Sabrina) (mpl). (Entered: 05/04/2018)\n05/09/2018 69 SENTENCING SUMMARY CHART & Certificate of Service by USA as to Joseph Saucedo (Feve, Sabrina) (mpl). (Entered: 05/09/2018)\n05/10/2018 70 Sentencing Document: Letter of Recommendation by Joseph Saucedo (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit)(Garcia, Mayra) (mpl). (Entered:\n05/10/2018)\n05/10/2018 71 OBJECTION and Response to Part of Government's Sentencing Memorandum by Joseph Saucedo re 68 Sentencing Memorandum (Garcia,\nMayra) (mpl). (Entered: 05/10/2018)\n05/10/2018 72 Sentencing Document: Response to Motion (see ECF No. 71) by USA as to Joseph Saucedo (Feve, Sabrina) (mpl). (Entered: 05/10/2018)\n05/11/2018 73 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Janis L. Sammartino: Sentence With PSR Hearing for Joseph Saucedo (1) on Count(s) 1\nand 2 of the Superseding Information. Custody of the BOP for 235 months as to each count 1 and 2 to run concurrent for a total of 235\nmonths. Supervised release for 20 years as to each count 1 and 2 to run concurrent for a total of 20 years. Court imposes no assessment, fine\nor restitution. Underlying Information dismissed on Govt's oral motion (Court Reporter/ECR Frank Rangus / CRD A Ramos / USPO C\nCassut / AUSA Sabrina L. Feve / CJA Mayra L. Garcia) (no document attached) (acr) (Entered: 05/11/2018)\n05/18/2018 74 JUDGMENT as to Joseph Saucedo (1), Count(s) 1, 2, Dismissed on Govt's oral motion; Count(s) 1s-2s, Custody of the BOP for 235\nmonths as to each count 1 and 2 to run concurrent for a total of 235 months. Supervised release for 20 years as to each count 1 and 2 to run\nconcurrent for a total of 20 years. Court imposes no assessment, fine or restitution. Signed by Judge Janis L. Sammartino. (mpl) (jao).\n(Entered: 05/18/2018)\n05/29/2020 75 MOTION to Appoint Counsel by Joseph Saucedo. (jpp) (Entered: 06/16/2020)\n02/10/2023 76 ORDER Denying 75 Defendant's Motion for Appointment of Counsel as to Joseph Saucedo (1). Signed by Judge Janis L. Sammartino on\n2/10/2023.(ave) (Entered: 02/10/2023)\n\nPACER Service Center\nTransaction Receipt\n06/23/2026 04:57:38\nPACER\nmrinaal_ramachandran Client Code:\nLogin:\nSearch 3:17-cr-00095-\nDescription: Docket Report\nCriteria: JLS\nBillable\n8 Cost: 0.80\nPages:"
